\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Did she have any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 No, she looked after her father. I'll tell you the story, my father - they lived in Taibach in the old Woofield Row. And my 
mother - my mothers sister, Sarah - looked after her father, and the mother dies, and she got married and went to \{BLANK\}
 to live. My mother and father went back to Margam to look after her father. And I must have been about seven or eight years of age then. That's the story of - why - why we went back to Cwmbrombil you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 So she didn't work at all really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 No, she was - looking after her father you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 I wonder if you could remember life at home when you were a child, it would be at Cwmbr
ombil. Would you remember what the house was like? How many rooms were in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 One room down and one room up. And there was a - a sl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3696877\charrsid10955930 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 pe - at the end you see, my mother used to do her washing and so on and so on, fireplace there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Like a lean-to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
A lean-to. At - at the end of the house, and coal house there one end and a lean-to the other end. But - one room upstairs and one room downstairs, bed downstairs see. Bed downstairs for two or three you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Did anybody else live in the house besides your parents and yourself and your sisters?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Not your grandparents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 No, no, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 My grandfather died - my grandfather died soon after we went - went back to live there. 'Course there's only - myself and the other - 
children, were three - three children then. Three children we were going back - going back to Brombil.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What had happened to the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 That wasn't born see, Maggie was born in Cwmbrombil.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Did your mother pay anyone to help - in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Never sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Did your mother or father mend or make the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh not - not make. Repair of course. Didn't make.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 They wouldn't make any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 No. Well - I think mother would then, make garments for the girls and so on. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Would your father do anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Mend any clothes or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 No. He was more of a choir man. And a bandsman. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Would you have new clothes or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh new clothes. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Do you remember where they were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
Where? Where? Oh there was a traveller coming around, you see, traveller coming around. Like they used to do then in the countries, used to pay so much a week see towards something and then they'd - bring the clothes you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 When would you have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 When - when? When? Oh we would - when we needed them of course, when we needed them. Ah.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Would you have new shoes or would you have secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
Oh new shoes. And the - and the same system again. There's a man coming around, Mills his name was. He used to come around to the - Margam, and - supply the - family with shoes and used to pay then every week do you see, that's - that's - that's the cus
tom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh more or less of course. More or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Would he help to clean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Yes, more or less, when he'd have time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What about cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh mother's for cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What about washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Well I couldn't say, we - we children used to wash up. We used to wash up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What about making the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Mother and father between them I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What about decorating or doing any repairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh well mother would do most of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh he'd be too busy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 He wouldn't do anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Well, he wouldn't do it - I mean occasionally he - he'd give a hand probably. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What about improvements to the home, if you wanted anything done, would your father do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Improvements of the home? Mm - it was done by the estate men. But any small job my grandfather or my father of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Would your father ever dress you or undress you when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Probably would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Do you remember him ever caring for you like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh he'd - give a hand of course when we were children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Would he bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 I don't remember much about bathing. And mother of course would be doing that, mother would do that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What about reading to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Did your father read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
Read to us? He was - oh yes, he was very fond - he used to - take a lot of interest in our education. I'll tell you one story now, when I used to take homework home - I'd an uncle in the - \{BLANK\}
 remember Uncle John, John Mainwaring Meg? Well now, he used to take me from our house to Donnon, all the way to Donnon, to solve a sum if - neither of us could do it - I shouldn't go to school next morning withou
t that some done. And Mr Bennet I remember now - \{BLANK\} at the time - to go all the way to Donnon to Uncle John to do this sum. I shouldn't go to school - unless this sum was done. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Would he tell you stories, or anything like that, your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
Oh yes, take interest in us, yes, yes. More music, band - man - band - etc. He was a great bandsman. Your father - your father - we had a phonograph in our house, all the old - \{BLANK\} Grandfather's you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Would your father ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh yes. Yes. For walks. Any - anything on in the town here. That's all. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 This is when you were a little child he would take you would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Probably would, 'cos you - I was in Taibach until I was seven. He - I was in Taibach now at seven years of age. Then we went back to the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Rhondda{\*\xmlclose} you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Where did you live in Taibach then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 In - Woodfield Row. Bought a house in Woodfield Row, of course all street is down now, remember it, remember the old Woodfield?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 So Woodfield Row you were born really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 No, in Brombil I was born. Brombil born. Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 So really it's about Woodfield Row we ought to talk perhaps? Or do you remember Brombil better?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 'Tis there I spent my childhood, more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 In Woodfield?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Yes, in Woodfield Row - Woodfield.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Do you remember what sort of house that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
Ah, we lived in the back portion of - the back portion of the house and - bottom of the house, that'd be like a - an extra part of it you know, like a back kitchen and a - and a bedroom. We lived in the back - in the back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Who was in the rest of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 A gentleman the name of Mr Lewis. Glynn Lewis. And he - he worked - he worked in - in - in Rodericks, in - in Rodericks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 In the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 In the mill, Rodericks mill. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 So you just had the one room down and the one room up then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 How many of you would be there then, your father and your mother, you and three girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 The two girls. Two girls. Yes. Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What happened if your mother went out, would your father look after you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
Probably. She - she didn't go out a lot. Not - not - not in the evenings. No. No. My father used to go out - often between - between the choir - be
tween the choir or something like that and the band practice, he wasn't home very often in the evening. No, no. He'd be - be home Saturday night - Saturday probably you see but in the week night of course they were - that was the custom then, choir practi
ce and band practice see. Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Did you when you were a little boy have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Did you have any little jobs to do now in the house to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
Oh very likely. We used to collect firewood. Firewood in the wood. You see, have coal you see, father's a miner. Used to get the coal. And then for wood, we used to collect the wood in the wood - in the big wood in Margam. Margam, perhaps in Gr
oes you know, the back of Groes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 You mentioned earlier now that you used to help with the washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Would you do that regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 You would or the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 I expect I had to do my share.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Would there be any other little jobs you know you'd have to do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
Oh the garden. When I got old enough, when I got old - strong enough, I had to spend a - a lot of time in the garden. Brought up in the garden do you see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 How long would you do those jobs until you you know all the time you were in school or?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh yes, 'til I started work probably. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 After you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 After I left school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What about your sisters, would they have jobs to do around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh yes, they would do - do their share of course. Do their share in the housework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Do you remember helping the girls, because you were older than the little, ever to dress or to feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 There wasn't all that between them you see was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Mm. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time when you were in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
Probably. Probably, yes, you had to go to bed. I would say a specific time, I will say that. But you - you - we - we wasn't late, it wasn't late, no. My father used
 to go to - what was on - pit top at six o'clock in the morning, and leave the house - of course they - used to go to bed earlier you see. Different to now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Did your mother or anybody else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh when we were small of course. Like every other mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Have you got an idea now what age you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh no, can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Did you share the bedroom or the bed with anybody?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Did you share the bedroom or the bed with anybody when you were a little boy now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
I'm not quite sure, of course we - used to manage between us anyhow. There were two beds, or two or three beds see, small beds. Small bed for the girls, I think I was sleeping on my own often. The girls in a small bed of their own see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Do you remember how often you bathed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Every weekend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Every weekend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 In the kitchen. In one room, in one room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh downstairs, in - in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 In the same room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Same room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Not in the lean-to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 No. No, that kept for washing. Washing that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What sort of cooking equipment did she have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh - always a - coal fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Was it a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
No. No range. No. All done on the coal fire. Saucepans and frying pan and so on, yes, oh yes, and - and - boiled all her - washing, she used to wash in the kitchen very often, at
 the bench, kitchen and wash - wash there for the whole lot of us. Mm. But women used to manage wonderful then. Mm. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Before we went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 You mentioned just now that your father had to be at the pit head at six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
Oh ah he was going early and mother - mother went back to bed after that. After the - put my - put my father off to bed - to school - to work, she'd go back - back to bed then for an hour or two. And I used to leave - in time to be at school b
y nine - say nine. And very strange - we were a number of boys from that area, and a number of boys from Goitra - going to that - that school, and we were the first there as a rule. And Mr Mart - remember Mr Martin - before your time, the day master, used
 to - tell the other boys, the long distance boys - were there first. Used to start early you see. Yes - mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What time would you have your breakfast then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh - eight to half past.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What members of the family would be present when you were having your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
Oh they'd be after me of course. The girls were going to Groes. They went to Groes. I went to Taibach school. Now Vyvyan at that time - he ran Taibach. The miners used to pay so much a week - for our education, tuppence or somethi
ng, used to pay our tuppence every Monday morning. And - the - the I think that was one reason that I went to Taibach school, because he had to pay for me you see, every miner - had to pay so much for their boys, the children. And I used to bring - provis
ions home do you see, from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Preston{\*\xmlclose}'s shop. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Preston{\*\xmlclose} had a shop then. Just opposite the old police station in Club Row. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}Preston{\*\xmlclose} had a shop then. And I used to take provisions home you see from school do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 But the girls didn't go to Taibach school did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 They - went to - went to Margam, to Groes school, they didn't go Taibach at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 You didn't go to Groes school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 No. Didn't go to Groes, no. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 So your father had his breakfast with your mother, then you would have your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Then the girls would have theirs after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Because they were going much nearer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Yes. Go to Groes then. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What did you usually have to eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Tea. Well I can't remember
 now exactly. It was mostly - mostly - home cooked do you see, home cooked and home - home made, home made bread, home made tart and cake, and we used to - keep two pigs for the year, and had a - mother had fowls one time. Had plenty - plenty of food of t
hat kind. Eggs. Bacon. Plenty of that kind of food. And - home made you see, mostly home made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Would you have anything different on certain days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Well Sun - Sundays. Sun - Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What would the difference be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh fresh meat on Sundays
 you see. Well for everyone of course. You'd a butchers shop in Taibach, next door to where the police station is now, can you hear me? There was a butchers shop then next door to the police station now - where the present police station. There was a drap
e
rs shop where the police station is now, Thomas. Thomas's shop they used to call it. And then the butchers shop was kept - by a butcher living in Kengighill, Pen'y-Bryn, their farm, and kept a butchers shop. My mother used to buy meat there on - there wer
e only two shops in Taibach then, Haycock and - this - this shop. Thomas wasn't it. Evan Thomas. Evan Thomas. Evan Thomas. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 So you'd have that on Sunday would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh we'd have fresh meat on Sunday. Of course we had plenty of - poultry do you 
see. It was nothing for mother to go - go out and kill a cockerel. Plen - plen - and when the hens would go out to - to - to - lay, have a dozen eggs say, they'd - sit on them, and they'd come down then with a dozen chicks. And probably they're cockerels,
 half cockerels among them mother would rear them then, and - nothing for my mother to kill a fowl in the week. We'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3696877\charrsid10955930 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
lenty of - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3696877\charrsid10955930 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 lenty you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What about the midday meal then at that time, what about your midday meal? Dinner hour you know, midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh take it to school. Take school - take school - take it to school every day. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Then would you have a meal in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 I'd just come home then. That - that - that would be the meal of the day like see in the evening - the evening mea
l do you see. My mother'd make - father would be coming home - just before that, and then we children we come from school you see. That would be the meal then, the main meal you could say of the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Your father would work what six in the morning until?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 To about five I expect. Five o'clock or - that time then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What did you have to drink at those meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh tea mostly. Mm. Tea or cocoa and coffee of course. But tea mostly. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 You mentioned just now that your mother baked her own bread, that was always the case was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Yes, her own bread. Her own - tart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
Jam, yes. 'Cos we used garden - we'd a good garden. You could grow enough gooseberries - gooseberries - currants, make our own jam, currant jam, currants, gooseberries - and so on, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Would she bottle the fruit at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 No, not used to bottle vegetables, only fruit.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Would she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Yes. Pickled - oh yes, and make - onion pickles etc, etc you know. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Would she make any wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
No, she didn't have any wine no. Used to to make wine. Let me see. Make rhubarb - yes, rhubarb wine. Yes, we used rhubarb wine, yes, yes. Yes, rhubarb wine. Used to grow a nice bed of rhubarb.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 What about medicines, did she make any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Mm - she done all kind of medicine you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Would there be any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Mm? No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 No diod faen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 No, nothing of that sort, no. No. If you were ill you know she had her - her way of - curing us. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh yes, quite a large garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Did they buy any at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Vegetables? No.
