I don't think so. No, we had very good staff - teacher staff. I don't think they - made any effort to make any distinction, no, I don't think so. In our cla
ss - we were the same boys just all along. You were treated very kindly, very kindly, and considerately now - oh yes, we didn't have some - no distinction, no. Ability. See, if you was a smart boy you would be - you'd be - considered wouldn't you, teacher
s do that don't they. A smart child - they seem to - lean towards them somehow don't they. Ah. Encourage him, encourage him more than - mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 You felt that? What about the others that weren't so smart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Oh well they used to take their chances then s
ee. 'Course the teacher didn't have the time to - to - consider each one did he. No. OH but on the whole I think you were all right. We didn't have what they call - a dunce didn't have a dunce in - no. You can't say you had a dunce, no. They varied of cou
rse, we all varied. In our different - aspects, but - oh no, we were a good class. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13836759 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452723 GM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 Ten. Oh I'm sorry, twelve. Twelve.
