 when you leave school at twelve you're leaving - at a bad age. You're between aren't you. See from twelve on you seem to take more interest yourself - the things that really interest you. But - of course 
I had to leave school. And I felt then well I must do something. So while I was lodging with Mrs - Dutton, how old would I be - twenty-five, I was twenty-five then. So I used to go in the night or the evening to - Mr Hildred.
