ants were distributed. Were distributed in - little groups, you know a group - in the wood. Well you was there to feed them. Yes, give them their food up and water - and give them water, and feed them, and see that - no - no - what do you call - a - a dog
 
will come into the wood. Or an hawk. Sometime the hawk would come. Well then if you was there walking around, he wouldn't come do you see, you would frighten because - he'd - he'd see you, a - a person was walking around. But - hawk would come sometimes. 
Pro}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14953012\charrsid10955930 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13139658\charrsid10955930 
l around in the woods you know and they'd snap up a bird you know. And - protect the - protect the bird now, opening out in the morning. The covers off. Putting them back in the night. And feed the hen. See they had water, and so on, and you come to kno
w the hen and the birds and everything, they seem to know you. And then when they grew up then and able to fly as it were - take 'em to a cover then, and distribute them, different covers, covers we call the woods. They're there then and we fed them then 
ready for the shooting season. There's so many birds in each wood you know. Ah, that was the system do you see.
